parameters: Brachiocondor: Hey... Shark Duke. You've got a visitor...
Memimi: A visitor...? Over there, perhaps...?

Memimi: (Wow... such a rugged face and sharp gaze... Even
through his clothes, I can tell he has a strong chest...!!
No, no... this is bad... he's totally my type...)

Memimi: Ahh... um, what can I do for you...? Your contact...
RoIN ID, maybe...? Let me just get my smartphone...

???: No need to be flustered... Walking around the
underground city in an Orca Suit would certainly cause a
commotion. I wanted to have a quiet talk with you, so I came
in human form...
Memimi: !!!? You're... you're the Orca Mayor...!?

Orca Mayor: How's Shark Broccoli doing...? I contacted him
for the first time in 5 years, was he surprised?

Memimi: Tha... that, umm... Not at all scared!! Shark
Broccoli the Great Boss doesn't even consider someone like
you worth noticing!!!

Memimi: I don't know if you're an old acquaintance or what,
but the only thing in the Great Boss's sight is the peace of
the city!! Normally, it would be too much of a waste to even
spend time on someone like you! I'll take care of you
myself, so just tremble and wait!!

Orca Mayor: Hmph... that guy hasn't changed at all... such a
good-natured fool... never thinks about himself...

Orca Mayor: Hey... try to persuade him too, will ya? If 10
million isn't enough, I'll even give him a position at the
city hall... As a civil servant, his salary will be
secure... Tell him to quit the dark organization and live as
he pleases.

Memimi: Fool, as if the Great Boss would want to become a
civil servant now of all times...! No matter what kind of
sweet talk you come up with to extract the secret recipe for
that delicious powder, there's no way he would nod in
agreement!!

Orca Mayor: Delicious powder, huh... Hmph, right... that's
just an excuse... no...

Orca Mayor: Anyway, this is the final notice... If you join
me now... I'll let Shark Broccoli enjoy a life of luxury
too. Even the dream he crushed long ago... running a
wrestling organization can be done with tax money.

Orca Mayor: And you too... if you're his disciple, then
you're practically my junior as well. Since we're family,
I'll give you a scholarship and can write you a letter of
recommendation for university... It's definitely more
advantageous to join my side, right?

Memimi: Don't underestimate me... it's not about money
anymore! Even if I lose to you and become an AV actress!
It's still a billion trillion times better than joining
someone like you!!!

Orca Mayor: This stubbornness... feels like I'm talking to
Shark Broccoli himself... Both master and disciple reject
me...

Orca Mayor: Well... I didn't think it would go well
anyway... If you had come over to my side, then maybe...
like old times... no, it's impossible now... heh...

Orca Mayor: No more mercy... You're set for an AV debut...
Shark Broccoli will be beaten to a pulp. After extracting
the recipe for the powder, maybe I'll make him my personal
chef.

Orca Mayor: Let's meet at the match venue... I'll sink you
in 10 seconds...

Memimi: That's my line!! To think you could beat Shark
Broccoli the Great Boss... such an absurd fantasy! You're
the one who will be jobless by this time tomorrow, jobless!!

Brachiocondor: ...Orca Asparagus... isn't it enough
already...? Deep down, you care more about... being together
with Shark Broccoli again than money...

Orca Mayor: Don't say another word!! Everything changed that
day... for us and for you too!! I'm not apologizing... I'm
right!
Orca Mayor: Hmph...! Send the bill to the city!

Bunny-chan: Hey Memimi-chan, that customer who just left was
really handsome! What kind of monster does he transform
into? Maybe he's been in one of the matches I refereed?

Brachiocondor: The next match is going to be the most
anticipated battle in Monster Fight history. As one of the
original fighters, it holds a lot of sentimental value for
me.

Memimi: Brachiocondor, along with Shark Broccoli-sama, was a
monster involved in the establishment of the Monster Fight
management committee.

Bunny-chan: I joined the management about a year ago, so I
don't really know much about the old days. Was the public
order worse before Monster Fight started?

Brachiocondor: ...5 years ago, when the mayor changed, a lot
of dark organizations sprang up in the city. Back then,
there were turf wars and conflicts everywhere.

Brachiocondor: Shark Broccoli and I were unbeatable in
fights, but hurting and trampling on others wasn't our
style... To avoid unnecessary conflicts, we ran around...
and refurbished an abandoned wrestling ring from a defunct
wrestling group...

Brachiocondor: Above all, we desired peace in the city. It
was our duty... especially since we were involved in the
events that led to the dark era of Doritoku City...

Bunny-chan: The veterans have quite complex histories, huh~.
The people at the headquarters don't really tell us much
about it...

Memimi: There's no need to pry... If the city becomes
peaceful, they might share their stories as tales of the
past. Let's show our predecessors a magnificent battle in
the next Monster Fight...

Memimi: But still, to think that the mayor of Dorobou City
was involved in Shark Broccoli's past... Brachiocondor, you
knew everything, didn't you?

Bunny-chan: It seems like things are pretty complicated, but
Orca Mayor defeated the previous mayor and took over Dorobou
City, right? I feel sorry for the previous mayor, just like
Shark Broccoli-san...

Brachiocondor: Sympathy is rather an insult... The previous
mayor also considered the future of the city in his own
way... It was quite difficult in this town with no notable
specialties or industries...

Memimi: Oh, Brachiocondor, you knew the previous mayor too?
You sure have a wide network... What is he doing now?

Brachiocondor: Well... let it be, that guy... he's probably
somewhere in the city, living energetically.

Bunny-chan: If the city's underworld organizations unite, I
wonder if they'll stop holding Monster Fights? It'll be a
bit lonely, but that would be proof that peace has been
achieved, right?

Memimi: I also like the atmosphere of the matches... I want
to preserve it in some form. There would be many monsters
who would be sad not to see Bunny-chan.

Bunny-chan: When I'm in my human form, I attend a so-called
lady's academy outside the city, but it's quite strict and
suffocating there... That's why I love the noisy and
boisterous Monster Fight arenas.

Memimi: That fervor is partly thanks to you, Bunny-chan...
The monsters running the show must be grateful...

Bunny-chan: Mayor Orca, that was scary~! I've never seen
such a tense and menacing villain before~. Memimi-chan,
please don't be reckless, okay...?

Memimi: That was the first time I've ever collided with a
body as solid as rock... But no matter what, I can't afford
to lose. This has become a matter of settling my life's
scores.

Bunny-chan: He's the bad guy who destroyed the orphanage
where Memimi-chan lived, right...? But you know~, if you
lose, you'll become an AV actress...? That's really not
okay, things like that...

Memimi: A retort for a retort... In the heat of the moment,
I carelessly... In every sense of the word, I've made it so
I can't afford to lose... I hate AV... I absolutely hate
it...

Brachiocondor: (Haven't there already been videos
circulating that are pretty much like AV...? Well, I'll keep
quiet about it...)
